SELECT 
    event_day AS day,
    emp_id,
    SUM(out_time - in_time) AS total_time
FROM 
    Employees
GROUP BY 
    event_day, emp_id;


SUM(out_time - in_time) AS total_time
Calculates the total time worked per employee per day.
✅ SUM(out_time - in_time)
This correctly calculates the duration an employee worked:

Copy
Edit
= 17:00 - 09:00
= 8 hours

❌ SUM(in_time - out_time)
This does the opposite:

Copy
Edit
= 09:00 - 17:00
= -8 hours (negative)
